# GitHub Package Registry Configuration
# Copy this file to .npmrc and replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN with your actual token

@sv-sdk:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}

# To create a GitHub token:
# 1. Go to GitHub Settings > Developer settings > Personal access tokens > Tokens (classic)
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a name like "sv-sdk-packages"
# 4. Select scopes: read:packages, write:packages, delete:packages
# 5. Click "Generate token" and copy the token
# 6. Set the token as an environment variable:
#    export GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here
# 7. Or replace ${GITHUB_TOKEN} above with your actual token (not recommended for security)

# For CI/CD (GitHub Actions):
# Add GITHUB_TOKEN as a repository secret and it will be automatically available

